# Feature Tracking in Notion

When you complete a significant feature or ship a major update for Dread.lol, create a row in the **Dread.Lol features** Notion database to track it.

## How

Use the create-database-row skill (or Notion MCP) with the **Dread.Lol features** database. Provide:

- **Name** — Feature name
- **Status** — `Done` (or Backlog/In Progress/Review as appropriate)
- **Priority** — Low, Medium, High, or Critical
- **Description** — One-line summary of what users get
- **Owner** — Assignee if known

## When

- New user-facing features (e.g. marketplace, gallery, new page)
- Major improvements to existing features
- Not: minor bug fixes, refactors, or internal changes

## Note

This is separate from the homepage updates list (`lib/updates.ts`). Both should be updated when shipping significant features.
